    The 5* hotel has been completely remodeled in a very tasteful way and while already very recently reopened will be inaugurated tomorrow.
    We were welcomed with delicious mint tea. The check in process handled by Ftima was very fast. She also provided excellent support organizing a tour and airport car service, always with a smile on her face.
    Our well-stocked room faced the Mediterranean Sea flanked by a very nice beach and promenade that we kept admiring from our balcony while sipping champagne.
    The bathroom was ample and the shower amazing. The bed big and the mattress so comfortable.
    We very much enjoyed the large pool and also the one on the 10th floor.
    The restaurant was superb. The food delicious, the service always outstanding. On a side note, the olive rolls are addictive. Don't miss them!
    The vibe and tapas and drinks in the bar on the top floor was a highlight. The DJ rhythms on a pleasant evening as well as the view of the bay are unbeatable.
    When in Tangier, stay here! We highly recommend this well-managed hotel. Our stay was unforgettable!

    Wonderful hotel in an amazing location, highly recommended!
    I wasnt sure at the beginning due to some comments here but the hotel has been remodelled and changed the management. Even they have opened recently I had an amazing experience.
    1. Lovely views to admire from my room on the first floor and even better from the rooftop.
    2. The food was delicious: great variety for breakfast with a mix of Moroccan, Spanish and European influenced food. I miss those breakfast and the fresh mint tea! I also enjoyed the couscous.
    3. Friendly staff. They spoke Spanish, English, French and Arabic. Very supportive at anytime (quick room service). They tried teaching me Arabic but still on working process!
    4. Massive bed and very comfortable.
    5. Laundry was fast and well done. I never had my clothes as well ironed!
    6. I enjoyed the 4 bars. My favourite was the Champe to play snooker (billar).
    When in Tangier, stay here you wont regret it!

    2/5
    Quite disappointed, this is not a four-star hotel
    My experience at the Almohades hotel was quite disappointing, mostly because of 
    Quite disappointed, this is not a four-star hotel
    My experience at the Almohades hotel was quite disappointing, mostly because of the service. The stay was not expensive, about 40,00 but I do expect good service when staying at a four-star hotel.
    The rooms are nice and clean. No problem there. I really enjoyed the bath tub and I slept very comfortably in the beds. There were good room service options, although nothing for vegans. Once I got to the room I did have to call the reception desk again to ask for towels and an extra key. This all took a little longer than it should.
    I spent a great night at the hotel. They have a bar, which seemed to be more festive than most parts of Tangier. It has also been the only place where I have been served alcohol. Im not sure about the location because it was quite far away from the medina, but we did have a sea view. It was so windy, however, that the sea front location was more of a problem to us.
    The upsetting part for me was the check out the next day. I was trying to hire a car and was unable to find one. The hotel did one attempt of calling the Hertz office at the airport but said they were closed. After that the staff has been of no further help. I expect a four-star hotel to help with such things and at least put a considerable amount of effort into it. I also did not receive an apology for their lack of service at all.
    It was not until three and a half hours later-we were still sitting in the lobby trying to find a solution-that a staff member came over and asked us if she could get us a taxi. At that point we had already found a driver ourselves.
    Pros:
    - Comfortable beds
    - Sea view
    - Enjoyed the bath tub
    - Good bar
    Cons:
    - Had to call the reception desk for towels
    - Staff did not apologize or empathize
    - Staff did not properly help us to find a rental car
    - Location quite a walk from the medina

    About this hotel

    A 4-minute walk from Tanger Beach, this sophisticated hotel is 13 km from Tangier Ibn Battouta Airport.

    Airy, relaxed rooms feature flat-screen TVs, free Wi-Fi and sitting areas, as well as furnished balconies. Some offer beach views.

    Amenities include a beachfront Lebanese restaurant and a modern eatery. Theres also a bar and a hip nightclub. The hotel also has an outdoor pool flanked by sunloungers. Parking is available for a surcharge.
